---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service - IPPriv | Usage Terms and Conditions"
  description="Read IPPriv's terms of service to understand the rules and guidelines for using our IP lookup and privacy tools."
  keywords="terms of service, usage terms, IPPriv terms, service conditions, legal terms"
  type="article"
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <article class="animate-fade-in">
        <header class="text-center mb-12">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 gradient-text">
            Terms of Service
          </h1>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Effective date: December 2024</p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              By accessing or using IPPriv's services, you agree to be bound by these 
              Terms of Service. If you disagree with any part of these terms, you may 
              not access our services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">2. Description of Services</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              IPPriv provides IP lookup, geolocation, VPN detection, and related 
              privacy tools through our website and API. We reserve the right to 
              modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of our services at any time.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">3. API Usage</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2 text-foreground">3.1 Rate Limits</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Free API access is subject to rate limits. Exceeding these limits may 
              result in temporary or permanent suspension of access.
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2 text-foreground">3.2 Prohibited Uses</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              You may not use our API for:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li>Illegal activities or purposes</li>
              <li>Harassment, stalking, or tracking individuals</li>
              <li>Spamming or distributing malware</li>
              <li>Circumventing security measures</li>
              <li>Reselling our services without authorization</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">4. User Accounts</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              If you create an account, you are responsible for maintaining its 
              security and all activities under your account. You must provide 
              accurate information and notify us of any unauthorized use.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              All content, features, and functionality of our services are owned by 
              IPPriv and are protected by international copyright, trademark, and 
              other intellectual property laws.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">6. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              Our services are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. 
              We do not guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or reliability of 
              any information provided through our services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              IPPriv shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, 
              consequential, or punitive damages resulting from your use of our 
              services or inability to use our services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">8. Changes to Terms</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              We may revise these terms at any time. Continued use of our services 
              after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-foreground">9. Contact</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
              For questions about these Terms, contact us at{" "}
              <a href="mailto:legal@ippriv.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">
                legal@ippriv.com
              </a>
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
